The paper focuses on the development of an automatic Android malware detection framework using deep learning techniques. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as the primary objective is to detect and prevent malicious attacks on Android devices. Additionally, the paper utilizes deep learning techniques for sequence classification, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning also involves training and learning from large datasets, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for portable and ubiquitous malware detection systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the processing and analysis of large datasets, which is a common theme in data science (cs.DS).
